Add Members to a Swarm in Lightning Experience

You can add members to an ongoing swarm by using Expert Finder or adding people directly, by name. When using Expert Finder, Omni-Channel routes invitations to the best available user with the specified skills and creates swarm member records for the case and swarm.

To add specific team members, select the corresponding option, enter their name where prompted, and see Considerations for Adding Swarm Members. To add team members via Expert Finder, select the corresponding option, choose the skills needed to complete the swarm, and Omni-Channel will find a qualified agent with capacity to assist.

The expert agent receives a swarm member request that they can accept or reject. Use this flow to add more than one new member to the swarm by repeating the process until the swarm is filled. When finished, click Next.

Omni-Channel routes your swarm request record to other available agents with capacity that match your skills specifications. When a swarm member is created, the case owner is assigned as the owner by default. To view the swarm and swarm members, see the recordâ€™s Swarm Members and Swarms related lists.
title: Adding Members to a Swarm in Service Cloud
